					.dmpage-text
						p Since 2020, PJSC TATNEFT Group has been working on a project to implement an automated system of ambient air quality monitoring in the territory of the Republic of Tatarstan. As of today, 27 units of stationary environmental checkpoints located in Almetyevsk, as well as near the settlements of Almetyevsk, Bavlinsky, Sarmanovsky, Zainsky, Bugulminsky, Cheremshansky districts have been put into operation. The Company also cooperates with the Ministry of Ecology and Natural Resources of the Republic of Tatarstan to identify and quickly eliminate sources of ambient air pollution at the Company's adjacent facilities when a signal is received from automatic air pollution control stations. To expand the monitoring system in 2022, 7 units of stationary environmental checkpoints were set up on the territory of the Republic of Tatarstan.
						p To inform the residents of Almetyevsk about the quality of ambient air, there are stands displaying indicators of ambient air pollution showing acceptable levels of air pollution in the city. Besides, information from the stationary environmental checkpoints installed inside Almetyevsk is transmitted to the website zachistyalmetyevsk.rf  24 hours a day.
						p To measure ambient air quality, the Company also uses mobile environmental control laboratories.

						
